	DAMAGE.

	That install applies to "Paperboy" © 1989 Elite.

	That install requires WHDLoad and RawDIC to be in the path.
	Both can be found in the whdload package.
	To install from a different drive than DF0: select Expert as
	installation mode.

	You can quit the game by pressing F10 (key can be changed with
	Tooltype "QuitKey=")

 Version 1.3 () done by JOTD:
 - slave rewritten for whdload 17, JST macros dropped
 - source code included
 
 Version 1.2 (07.10.2001) done by JOTD:
 - Coded RawDIC imager (The old ripper did not work)
   Disk imaging must be re-done for that version. The file "bootblock" is
   no longer necessary.

 Version 1.1 (??) done by JOTD:
 - Quickly converted to WHDLoad (using Harry macros)
 - Game runs from HD using WHDLoad (gave up JST)
 - Lots of SNOOP bugs fixed
 - QUITKEY
 - Nice icon by Frank
 - BUTTONWAIT added to let you see the title picture

 
 Version 1.0 (??.08.1998) done by Ralf:
 - First official release (JST)


